Saudi Corporate Bad Loans Were $1.8 Billion, Eqtisadiah Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-04-24T10:34:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/saudi-corporate-bad-loans-were-1-8-billion-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia  had 6.6 billion riyals
($1.8 billion) in non-performing corporate loans, or 1.2 percent
of total corporate lending, at the end of February,  Al
Eqtisadiah  reported, citing the  Saudi Credit Bureau  chairman.  Bad retail loans amounted to 2.5 billion riyals, or 10.7
percent of all retail lending, the newspaper cited Nabil Al
Mubarak as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  